hook.real_world_problem:
Swiggy's order service handles three concurrent features: payment processing (critical), order tracking (heavy polling), restaurant discovery (read-heavy). Without bulkheads:

```
500 order tracking requests × 3 seconds each = 1500 thread-seconds
Thread pool: 200 threads (all blocked on tracking)
Payment requests: waiting for a free thread → timeout → payment FAILS
```

```java
// WITH bulkheads:
@Bulkhead(name="tracking",    fallbackMethod="cachedTracking")
// max 100 concurrent tracking calls → remaining 100 threads for payments!
@Bulkhead(name="payments",    fallbackMethod="paymentBusy")
// max 50 concurrent payment calls → isolated, protected
```

concept_explanation.bulkhead_types:
**Semaphore vs Thread Pool Bulkhead:**

```yaml
resilience4j:
  bulkhead:
    instances:
      tracking:
        maxConcurrentCalls: 100       # semaphore: max concurrent calls
        maxWaitDuration: 500ms        # wait up to 500ms for a permit
  thread-pool-bulkhead:
    instances:
      payments:
        maxThreadPoolSize: 50         # dedicated thread pool for payments
        coreThreadPoolSize: 20
        queueCapacity: 10
        keepAliveDuration: 20ms
```

```java
// Semaphore bulkhead — blocks the calling thread:
@Bulkhead(name = "tracking", fallbackMethod = "cachedTracking")
public TrackingUpdate getOrderTracking(String orderId) {
    return trackingClient.fetch(orderId);
}
private TrackingUpdate cachedTracking(String id, BulkheadFullException e) {
    return TrackingUpdate.cached(id);  // return last known position
}

// Thread pool bulkhead — executes in a dedicated thread pool:
@Bulkhead(name = "payments", type = Bulkhead.Type.THREADPOOL)
public CompletableFuture<PaymentResult> processPayment(PaymentRequest req) {
    return CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> paymentClient.process(req));
    // Runs in the 'payments' thread pool (max 50 threads)
    // Calling thread returns immediately
}
```

